[{"category":"section","location":"#SparsityProbes","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for SparsityProbes.\n\n","title":"SparsityProbes"},{"category":"type","location":"#SparsityProbes.ChunkedDetector","page":"Home","text":"ChunkedDetector(chunk_size::Int)\n\nA detector configuration for ADTypes.jacobian_sparsity that computes the  sparsity pattern in blocks of a given chunk_size to optimize memory overhead.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SparsityProbes.ChunkedDetector"},{"category":"method","location":"#ADTypes.jacobian_sparsity-Tuple{Any, Any, SparsityProbes.ChunkedDetector}","page":"Home","text":"ADTypes.jacobian_sparsity(f, x, detector::ChunkedDetector)\n\nCompute the Jacobian sparsity pattern of a function f at input x using  a chunked tracking strategy.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ADTypes.jacobian_sparsity"},{"category":"method","location":"#SparsityProbes.combine_patterns-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:AbstractMatrix}}","page":"Home","text":"combine_patterns(patterns::AbstractVector{<:AbstractMatrix})\n\nMerge a sequence of partial sparsity pattern matrices into a single sparsity pattern matrix by performing an element-wise logical OR operation across all matrices.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SparsityProbes.combine_patterns"},{"category":"method","location":"#SparsityProbes.create_chunks-Tuple{AbstractArray, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"create_chunks(x::AbstractArray, chunk_size::Int)\n\nSplit the linear indices of array x into a vector of ranges based on chunk_size.  Handles uneven edge cases and chunk sizes larger than the array length.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SparsityProbes.create_chunks"},{"category":"method","location":"#SparsityProbes.trace_input_chunk-Tuple{Type{SparseConnectivityTracer.GradientTracer{Int64, BitSet}}, AbstractArray, UnitRange{Int64}}","page":"Home","text":"trace_input_chunk(T::Type{<:GradientTracer}, x::AbstractArray, chunk::UnitRange{Int})\n\nInitialize a dual-number vector xt where only the indices belonging to chunk  are seeded with active tracers. All other indices are filled with empty tracers.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"SparsityProbes.trace_input_chunk"}]
